-- Limited December same-store sales down 8 percent
-- 
-- Thu Jan 10, 2008 7:20am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/10/businesspro-usa-retailsales-limited-dc-idUSWNAS610120080110

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Limited Brands Inc ( LTD.N ) said on 
Thursday sales at stores open at least a year fell 8 percent in 
December. 

  Analysts, on average, had expected a same-store sales 
decline of 4.1 percent over the five weeks ended January 5, 
according to Reuters Estimates.  Net sales for the operator of the Victoria's Secret and 
Bath & Body Works chains were $1.74 billion, compared with 
$2.03 billion in the same period last year.  (Reporting by  Alexandria Sage ; Editing by Steve Orlofsky)